How to run locally

Ensure you have Node.js, npm, git, and an IDE such as VS Code installed.

Node.js and npm install guide: https://nodejs.org/en/download/
Git install: https://git-scm.com/downloads
VS Code install: https://code.visualstudio.com/

------------------------------
Installation and Setup Steps
------------------------------

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/azlannaeem/csc309-a3.git

2. Install frontend dependencies:
   cd frontend
   npm install

3. Install backend dependencies:
   cd ../backend
   npm install

4. Set up Prisma:
   npx prisma generate
   npx prisma db push
   npm run seed   # (This command populates the database but you can edit the seed file if needed)

5. Start the backend server:
   node index.js 3000

6. In a new terminal, start the frontend app:
   cd frontend
   npm run dev

You now have a locally running loyalty program application.

------------------------------
Additional Package Information
------------------------------
- Multer is used for file uploads
- qrcode.react is used for QR code generation